author: Scott Manley
description:
Another packed update full of spaceflight and rocket launch stories. The Big news is that Jared Isaacman is once again nominated for NASA Administrator. Also, There are a few important rocket launches, the X-59 makes its first flight. Blue Origin gets ready for flight #2 of New Glenn, and somewhere in there I played a DJ set in the KSC rocket garden while wearing a Kilt.

Follow me on Twitter for more updates:
https://twitter.com/DJSnM

title: Seize The Night! - FAA Bans Daytime Rocket Launches - Deep Space Update - November 67th
